  "body": "**What would you like to be added**:\r\nAdd an annotation to allow lookup of loadBalancerIP by specifying a named Azure resource instead of an explicit IP address. This can pair with the existing 'azure-load-balancer-resource-group' annotation (perhaps call it 'azure-load-balancer-public-ip-resource' or similar).\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\nDuring provisioning of k8s clusters on Azure we request IP addresses with specific tags from an Azure IP allocation service. As a result we do not know at cluster setup time what address we will receive, but we do know what the name of the resource is as we control this. While possible to look up the IP during YAML generation it feels more appropriate to extend this functionality within k8s itself.\r\n\r\nIn https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/b6c8ef298ebfceb66422c416f55ab6076b7ff65d/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/azure/azure_loadbalancer.go#L213 it appears an attempt is made to do a reverse lookup from IP address to resource anyway so this would just save time/effort.\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-azure-feature-requests",
